README BACKEND FILE
EcoFinds Backend

EcoFinds is a sustainable second-hand marketplace built to encourage responsible consumption by making it simple to buy and sell pre-owned items.
This backend powers core functionalities such as user authentication, product listings, browsing, cart management, and purchase history.

🚀 Features

User Authentication: Register, login, and manage user profiles.

Product Listings (CRUD): Create, read, update, and delete products.

Search & Filtering: Browse listings with keyword search and category filtering.

Cart Management: Add/remove products from the cart.

Purchase History: Track previous purchases.

REST API: Provides endpoints for frontend (web/mobile) integration.

🛠️ Tech Stack

Backend Framework: Django/ FastAPI 

Database: postgreSQL

Authentication: JWT / Session-based

Language: Python

backend/
│── app/                  # Main application folder
│   ├── routes/           # API routes (users, products, cart, etc.)
│   ├── models/           # Database models
│   ├── services/         # Business logic
│   ├── utils/            # Helper functions (auth, validation, etc.)
│   └── __init__.py
│
│── migrations/           # DB migrations (if used)
│── requirements.txt      # Python dependencies
│── config.py             # Configuration (DB, secrets, etc.)
│── run.py                # Entry point to start backend server
│── README.md             # This file

⚙️ Setup Instructions
1. Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/ecofinds.git
cd ecofinds/backend

2. Create Virtual Environment & Install Dependencies
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # On macOS/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate      # On Windows

pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Configure Environment Variables
Create a .env file in the backend folder:

SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key
DATABASE_URL=mysql://username:password@localhost/ecofinds
DEBUG=True

5. Start the Backend Server
python run.py

📡 API Endpoints
User

POST /auth/register → Register a new user

POST /auth/login → Login and get token

GET /users/me → Get current user profile

Products

POST /products/ → Create new product

GET /products/ → Get all products

GET /products/<id> → Get product by ID

PUT /products/<id> → Update product

DELETE /products/<id> → Delete product

Cart

POST /cart/add → Add product to cart

GET /cart/ → View cart items

DELETE /cart/remove/<id> → Remove item from cart

Purchases

GET /purchases/ → View previous purchase

